<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I'm creating a ActiveDirectory extension to the LDAP classes and noticed this bug. In the Zend_Ldap_Attribute class there is a method getDateTimeAttribute(). If the value returned by getAttribute() is an array it should work fine but if it's a single value (specified by the index) then the method doesn't check if _valueFromLdapDateTime() returned null.</p>

<p>Basically, just need to add a check for "non" array attributes that if <em>valueFromLdapDateTime() returns null to return the _original</em> value and not null.</p>

